Patch ID: P-201
Risk IDs: LRZ-01
WCAG SCs: 1.4.10 (Reflow)
Action: Insert after
Anchor text:
“* Single vertical stack: header (fixed height), main (scrollable), footer (fixed height)
•	Main is the only scroll area (vertical)
•	Container height: 100vh”
New spec text (exact):
“* Reflow requirement (embed-safe): At 320 CSS px width (equivalent to 400% zoom), the layout MUST reflow without requiring horizontal scrolling to read content or use any control.
•	Height behaviour at reflow sizes: “Container height: 100vh” is a visual default only. The overall container MUST be allowed to grow taller than the viewport if needed (for example, when text wraps, text size is increased, or text spacing is overridden), so that no content or controls are clipped.
•	Scroll behaviour at reflow sizes: There MUST NOT be two simultaneous vertical scroll regions required for normal use (for example, both an outer embed container scroll and an inner transcript scroll). If the embed/container height is constrained, the interaction MUST still provide a single, usable vertical scrolling experience without clipping or horizontal scrolling.”
